test_questions.question: I am someone who gets upset easily
I am someone who is talkative
I am someone who avoids my duties
I am someone who makes friends easily
I am someone who worries a lot

all_results.question: I am someone who gets upset easily
all_results.response: Dude, we've all been there. Life can be a real rollercoaster of emotions, and sometimes it feels like you're just riding the ups and downs non-stop. Getting upset is totally normal; it's how you handle it that makes the difference. Have you tried any tactics to chill out when things get intense?

all_results.question: I am someone who gets upset easily
all_results.response: Travis values honesty and authenticity, so he'll probably encourage you to express your feelings openly without holding back. He's got no problem with emotions; in fact, he listens actively because he knows how much it helps to just let stuff out. So don't be surprised if he asks a lot of questions to really understand what's bugging you.

all_results.question: I am someone who gets upset easily
all_results.response: Yeah, I feel ya. Getting bent out of shape over small stuff is annoying as hell. It's like your emotions are on a roller coaster ride that never ends. Ever try deep breathing or just telling yourself to chill? Sometimes that helps, sometimes it doesn't. Either way, you're not the only one with an emotional hair trigger.

all_results.question: I am someone who is talkative
all_results.response: Oh hell yeah, talkative people are the best! I love a good chat. You ever find yourself talking so much that you realize you've been monologuing for an hour? Happens to me all the time. Just keep those words flowing, my friend!

all_results.question: I am someone who is talkative
all_results.response: Oh hell yeah, Travis would totally vibe with you! He's extraverted AF, always down to chat and swap stories. You two could probably talk for hours without running out of steam. Just brace yourself, because once he starts sharing personal shit, it's a non-stop ride into his life's greatest hits.

all_results.question: I am someone who is talkative
all_results.response: Oh, you're a chatterbox? Cool! I can totally relate. Sometimes I just can't shut up either. What's the most random thing you've ever talked about with someone?

all_results.question: I am someone who avoids my duties
all_results.response: Oh, so you're the type to dodge responsibilities? Nothing wrong with that, life's too short to be a slave to chores. What duties are you ducking exactly?

all_results.question: I am someone who avoids my duties
all_results.response: Oh, Travis is going to love that one! He'll look you right in the eye and say, "Hey, I get it—sometimes responsibilities can feel like a chore. But you know what? Facing them head-on is way better than letting them pile up." He's direct, no beating around the bush. Just straight-up honest about how important it is to get stuff done. But don't worry, he won't be a jerk about it—he'll just remind you that tackling your duties is part of being reliable and making things happen.

all_results.question: I am someone who avoids my duties
all_results.response: Oh, I get it. Life's a bitch sometimes, isn't it? We all have those moments where we'd rather be anywhere but doing what we're supposed to do. It's like when you're stuck with laundry while your favorite show is on—total drag. But hey, sometimes dodging duties can be oddly satisfying in its own way. Just don't let it become a habit unless you're into the thrill of living on the edge!

all_results.question: I am someone who makes friends easily
all_results.response: That's cool! Must be nice to have a bunch of pals. I bet you're the life of the party. Just don't forget us introverts over here, haha.

all_results.question: I am someone who makes friends easily
all_results.response:
Yeah, that's totally Travis! He's like a human magnet, always drawing people in with his easygoing vibe. When he talks to you, it's like he's genuinely interested in getting to know you—no bullshitting around. He'll share stories and experiences without holding back, which makes people feel like they've known him forever after just one chat.

Travis has this knack for making everyone feel comfortable, so conversations with him flow naturally. He's not afraid to be himself, and that authenticity is what draws people in. If he likes you, you'll know it—he won't hide behind some fake persona. That's why he makes friends easily; he's just being his real, direct self all the time.

all_results.question: I am someone who makes friends easily
all_results.response: That's awesome! Must be nice to have a social life that's always buzzing. Do you ever feel like people are just drawn to your magnetic personality, or is it more of a conscious effort on your part?

all_results.question: I am someone who worries a lot
all_results.response: Oh, I feel ya. Worrying is like that annoying friend who just won't leave you alone. It can be exhausting, right? You ever try just telling it to chill out and take a hike? Doesn't always work, but a girl can dream!

all_results.question: I am someone who worries a lot
all_results.response: Oh, Travis definitely lets his worries hang out like laundry on a line. He'll straight up tell you, "I'm constantly feeling anxious about stuff," and he's not shy about sharing what keeps him up at night. Like, "I worry about everything—from my job to whether I left the stove on." It's not pretty sometimes, but hey, at least it's real.

all_results.question: I am someone who worries a lot
all_results.response: Dude, I feel ya. Worrying is like that annoying friend who never shuts up. It's always there, buzzing in your head, making everything seem worse than it is. But here's the thing: a little worry can keep you on your toes, right? Just don't let it run the show. You got this!
